  "texts": [
    "The performance comparison between the YOLOX model and radiologists was carried out on the held-out test dataset and the recombination test dataset.",
    "Three junior radiologists and three senior radiologists were asked to independently annotate all CXRs in the above two test datasets.",
    "On the held-out test dataset, when the IoU-T was set from 0.1 to 0.5 with a step of 0.1, it was clear that the F1-scores of the 14 chest abnormalities achieved by the YOLOX model were more stable than those of the six radiologists (Fig. 5).",
    "We can see the PR curves of the 14 abnormalities and the results obtained by the six radiologists with an IoU-T of 0.5 in Fig. 6.",
    "The mean precision, recall and F1-score obtained by the YOLOX model were 0.693, 0.651 and 0.665, respectively, which were higher than those of the best senior radiologist, whose values were 0.626, 0.547 and 0.577, respectively (Supplementary Table 10)."
